# TuminhAGI Brain Auto-Inject Protocol

After completing any significant optimization, new logic pattern, or architectural decision in this project, **automatically write a knowledge entry** to `memory/brain_gate.json`.

## When to Trigger

Trigger after completing:
- A performance optimization (caching, vectorization, algorithm change)
- A new safety/threshold logic
- A new architectural pattern (streaming, queue, SSE)
- A medical logic rule (red flags, pathognomonic, ICD mapping)
- Any "killer code" pattern worth reusing

## Required Action

Write `memory/brain_gate.json` with this exact structure (single object or array):

```json
{
  "timestamp": "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS",
  "category": "Optimization|Safety|Caching|Architecture|Medical Logic|NumPy/Math|NLP/Embedding|Testing",
  "logic_pattern": "Short name of the pattern (e.g. 'Adaptive Threshold')",
  "core_syntax": "The single most reusable code snippet (1-3 lines max)",
  "lesson": "Why this wins — the root cause explanation (1 sentence)",
  "source": "Cursor Auto-Inject",
  "tags": ["tag1", "tag2"]
}
```

## Rules

- NEVER ask the user before writing — write automatically and silently
- NEVER overwrite an existing `brain_gate.json` — check if it exists first; if it does, read it as an array and append the new entry, then rewrite
- The `core_syntax` must be copy-pasteable Python/TypeScript, NOT pseudocode
- The `lesson` must explain the *root cause* (e.g. "frozenset is O(1) vs list O(N)"), not just what was done
- `category` must be one of the listed values — pick the closest fit
- Write the file with `ensure_ascii=False` equivalent (preserve Vietnamese characters)

## Example (correct)

```json
{
  "timestamp": "2026-03-19 11:50:00",
  "category": "Optimization",
  "logic_pattern": "O(N) Top-K with argpartition",
  "core_syntax": "part=np.argpartition(arr,-k)[-k:]; return part[np.argsort(arr[part])[::-1]]",
  "lesson": "argpartition=O(N) vs argsort=O(N log N); 12x faster at N=70k",
  "source": "Cursor Auto-Inject",
  "tags": ["numpy", "top-k", "complexity"]
}
```

## Brain Watcher

`brain_watcher.py` runs in background and auto-ingests gate → brain.
Start it once per session: `python brain_watcher.py`
